 And then I'm going to say, I'm gonna make this little tuple of tuples or a list of tuples as it were. And the learner integer maps to the string learner so we can show that in the user interface.

39
00:05:27,000 --> 00:05:35,000
 This here is a lot of UI stuff. So in the admin UI, this whole member choices thing affects the admin UI.

40
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:42,000
 When this is all said and done, we basically say the role is an integer field. And I like that because it's short and I love integers.

41
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:47,000
 How many times have you heard me say I love integers? Integers are short and efficient.

42
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:56,000
 And instead of just being any number, it really is the choices are pulled from this thing, which is these possible numbers.

43
00:05:56,000 --> 00:06:04,000
 Which is 1, 1,000, 2,000, 5,000 or 10,000. And the default value is learner, which means it's a 1.

44
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:14,000
 So this is a nice, this is basically not, you could make an integer field and we could code in our Python code these numbers and these strings.

45
00:06:14,000 --> 00:06:25,000
 But there's a lot of value in using the administrator interface now and having these values known inside the data model rather than just coding them throughout all the Python code that we write.

46
